-- Taiwan's CTBC Financial says insurance unit to take 19.99 pct stake in Chinese life insurer
-- By J.R. Wu
-- Fri Aug 29, 2014 06:08AM EDT
-- None



TAIPEI, Aug 29 (Reuters) - Taiwan's CTBC Financial Holding Co Ltd <2891.TW> said Friday that its insurance unit was taking a 19.99 percent stake in a Chinese life insurer.

CTBC Life, the insurance unit of one of Taiwan's biggest private financial holding groups, will acquire the stake in ABC Life Insurance Co Ltd for 1.71 billion yuan ($278 million), the parent company said in a statement.